Yes, Lee Hong Ju is your problem now.

263
00:19:36,590 --> 00:19:39,510
I understand why you're like this because it's Lee Ddoong, but...

264
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:44,060
Wow! But I don't know if she will act as you predict.

265
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:46,700
- You're not even her type. 
 - Uncle!

266
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,960
I warned you, okay?

267
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:53,290
I warned you! All right?

268
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:04,390
 How was the blind date? 

269
00:20:04,390 --> 00:20:05,940
 The thing is— 

270
00:20:05,940 --> 00:20:08,880
Try meeting my niece if it didn't work out.

271
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:12,320
She just got a job, and she wants to get married.

272
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:13,890
She's 25 years old.

273
00:20:13,890 --> 00:20:16,630
I think you two would make such a nice couple.

274
00:20:16,630 --> 00:20:19,230
Gosh, Ma'am...

275
00:20:19,230 --> 00:20:21,080
Your niece wouldn't like me.

276
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:25,140
Gosh, I wouldn't just introduce her to anyone.

277
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:28,220
There's no one like you these days.

278
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:31,940
You're kindhearted, dependable, and clean-cut.

279
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:34,760
He has a full head of hair too.

280
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:37,400
By the way, Teacher Son has high standards.

281
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,010
Look. He won't even bat an eye at me.

282
00:20:40,010 --> 00:20:41,790
N-No, no, I...

283
00:20:41,790 --> 00:20:44,840
My niece is younger than you, Ms. Kim.

284
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:48,410
And she's a natural beauty like me.

285
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:51,370
Gosh, Teacher Oh.

286
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:55,510
That's so old school to mention being a natural beauty.

287
00:20:55,510 --> 00:20:58,610
Could you tell your niece

288
00:20:58,610 --> 00:21:03,020
to see a dermatologist once she gets her first paycheck?

289
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:07,970
Teacher Son, could we talk for a second?

290
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:22,700
Well, I didn't want to say this because it hurts my pride,

291
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:26,950
but why won't you ask Hong Ju out again?

292
00:21:27,670 --> 00:21:30,260
The thing is that I...

293
00:21:30,260 --> 00:21:31,920
I'm not saying this because she's my friend.

294
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:35,570
Her charm is like a black hole.

295
00:21:35,570 --> 00:21:38,820
Once you fall for her, there's no going back. That's why.

296
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:40,650
I can guarantee it, okay?

297
00:21:40,650 --> 00:21:45,020
Even I've been smitten with her for over a decade.

298
00:21:45,020 --> 00:21:50,780
Ms. Kim, she said she has no interest in dating.

299
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:56,650
What? She thought you weren't interested in her.

300
00:21:56,650 --> 00:21:59,370
Come on. It was just a misunderstanding.

301
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:01,300
Call Hong Ju right now, Teacher Son.

302
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:04,930
Teacher Kim, to be honest, I...

303
00:22:06,990 --> 00:22:08,920
Let's go.

304
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:12,870
Teacher Son,

305
00:22:12,870 --> 00:22:15,940
you can't go on another blind date, okay?

306
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:18,840
Her niece is weird.

307
00:22:23,390 --> 00:22:25,150
Okay.

308
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:37,470
   
   

309
00:22:37,470 --> 00:22:40,280
She parked here again.

310
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:44,100
How many times do I have to tell her?

311
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:46,600
Seriously.

312
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,920
   

313
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:54,250
 The customer is not answering the phone. After the beep... 

314
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:57,600
Okay, you won't answer?

315
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,920
Should I just crash into it?

316
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,630
I told her not to park here—

317
00:23:02,630 --> 00:23:05,070
   

318
00:23:08,170 --> 00:23:10,710
Yes, what's the matter?

319
00:23:10,710 --> 00:23:12,870
Did you look at the data Mr. Kang assembled?

320
00:23:12,870 --> 00:23:14,510
Yes.

321
00:23:14,510 --> 00:23:16,220
 It was completely faultless. 

322
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:18,770
 What more does he have to check that he postponed his departure? 

323
00:23:18,770 --> 00:23:20,680
I didn't like him from the beginning.

324
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,670
 He knows too well that he's superior. 

325
00:23:22,670 --> 00:23:25,630
To be honest, he is superior.

326
00:23:27,180 --> 00:23:30,030
Hey, so what if he's all that?

327
00:23:30,030 --> 00:23:33,400
 His head is probably filled with nothing but numbers. 

328
00:23:37,830 --> 00:23:40,680
This is how it went, right?

329
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,510
   

330
00:23:45,510 --> 00:23:49,370
   

331
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,610
He should have told me.

332
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:57,820
Hey.

333
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:00,910
What's with you?

334
00:24:00,910 --> 00:24:04,180
- What about me? 
 - You got promoted.

335
00:24:06,790 --> 00:24:09,960
Didn't you know?

336
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:12,850
Should I congratulate you or not?

337
00:24:12,850 --> 00:24:15,920
I heard the new office is owned by a prominent Korean family.

338
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,220
It hasn't been confirmed yet.

339
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:21,160
What do you mean? Your mom told me to send you back to HQ immediately.

340
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,680
I'll figure it out.

341
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:24,620
Where are you going?

342
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:28,580
You should have dinner, at least.

343
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:30,570
 Hu Yeong! 

344
00:24:38,130 --> 00:24:41,330
 Success or love? 

345
00:24:41,330 --> 00:24:45,750
 It's that cliche of a problem again. 

346
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:17,170
 Lee Hong Ju, I'm glad you're here. 

347
00:25:17,170 --> 00:25:22,970
 He's the one who almost turned you into a carp head, right? 

348
00:25:22,970 --> 00:25:26,010
 I have to keep ignoring this too, right? 

349
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:29,890
Ignoring would be better.

350
00:25:55,860 --> 00:25:59,180
Hey, Kang Hu Yeong. Funny to run into you here.

351
00:25:59,180 --> 00:26:00,840
Are you heading home, too?

352
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:04,520
We run into each other because we share the same route.

353
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:10,340
The property values went up a lot around here.

354
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:14,570
I should have bought a place a long time ago.

355
00:26:16,490 --> 00:26:18,750
Is your project in Korea going well?

356
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:20,690
It's going okay.

357
00:26:22,230 --> 00:26:25,460
When are you returning to the U.S.?

358
00:26:27,350 --> 00:26:29,140
I don't know.

359
00:26:30,630 --> 00:26:34,400
I suppose you never inform before leaving.

360
00:26:37,950 --> 00:26:39,860
Kang Hu Yeong,

361
00:26:42,550 --> 00:26:44,620
do you want fried chicken?

362
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,340
 I surprised you, didn't I? 

363
00:27:05,340 --> 00:27:08,530
You did. How could this happen?

364
00:27:08,530 --> 00:27:13,000
Are you really Uncle Wook's nephew?

365
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:18,550
We really must be meant to be, Hu Yeong.

366
00:27:18,550 --> 00:27:20,240
I know.

367
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:23,060
Unnie, we'll have a half order of spicy plus half order fried chicken and a coke.

368
00:27:23,060 --> 00:27:26,320
Why half and half? You always order a whole chicken per person.

369
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:28,660
I don't have an appetite. Right.

370
00:27:28,660 --> 00:27:30,380
You were craving fried chicken a lot, right?

371
00:27:30,380 --> 00:27:32,600
Should I order another one?

372
00:27:34,790 --> 00:27:37,150
Unnie, we'll have a whole one spicy and one plain.

373
00:27:37,150 --> 00:27:38,400
Okay.

374
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:41,520
Why don't you have an appetite? Did your boss yell at you again?

375
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:44,530
Why would she? I'm really good at my job.

376
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:48,490
 Then why would you lose an appetite you've had all your life? 

377
00:27:48,490 --> 00:27:50,450
What's wrong with her?

378
00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:54,560
I wouldn't know.

379
00:28:02,470 --> 00:28:04,900
So where did you run into each other?

380
00:28:04,900 --> 00:28:07,080
In front of work.

381
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:10,470
I noticed someone was following me secretly.

382
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:16,310
"Secretly"? You're giving her the wrong idea.

383
00:28:16,310 --> 00:28:18,580
You were walking ahead of me.

384
00:28:18,580 --> 00:28:21,950
All I did was walk behind you.

385
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:24,580
You tried to ignore me.

386
00:28:24,580 --> 00:28:27,670
I thought you were grateful I saved you earlier today.

387
00:28:27,670 --> 00:28:28,960
"Saved her"?

388
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:31,120
"Earlier today"? Why?

389
00:28:34,570 --> 00:28:37,130
I had no idea your leg was there.

390
00:28:37,130 --> 00:28:39,710
I suppose my legs are too long. Sorry.

391
00:28:39,710 --> 00:28:41,910
Lee Hong Ju, you...

392
00:28:42,970 --> 00:28:46,510
Why are you still the same as you were ten years ago?

393
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:48,600
What did I do?

394
00:28:50,110 --> 00:28:52,090
You still...

395
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:55,820
 are as clueless... 

396
00:28:58,760 --> 00:29:00,960
 and dumb as ever. 

397
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:06,360
You're calling me dumb to my face?

398
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:09,420
Wow. I took you on amusement rides yesterday,

399
00:29:09,420 --> 00:29:11,640
took photos of you, and entertained you all day.

400
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:14,800
Even today, since you said you wanted fried chicken,

401
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:18,930
I invited you when I planned to hang out alone with Hye Ji.

402
00:29:18,930 --> 00:29:21,820
I've been so nice to you, but you call me...

403
00:29:21,820 --> 00:29:24,610
clueless and dumb?

404
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:29,730
You're the one who's still freaking annoying, okay?

405
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:39,870
Excuse me. I'll have a draft beer.

406
00:29:39,870 --> 00:29:42,170
 Three? One? 

407
00:29:42,170 --> 00:29:44,800
No, cancel the draft beer.

408
00:29:47,330 --> 00:29:49,860
Ms. Kim, it's Monday today.

409
00:29:49,860 --> 00:29:52,320
We promised not to drink on Mondays.

410
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:55,540
I'll go to the restroom.

411
00:29:55,540 --> 00:29:57,950
Start eating without me.

412
00:29:57,950 --> 00:29:59,740
Enjoy it.

413
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:16,350
Hu Yeong,

414
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:20,480
I might be overreacting,

415
00:30:21,270 --> 00:30:24,980
but I need to clarify stuff like this.

416
00:30:27,970 --> 00:30:30,740
Do you like Hong Ju?

417
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:37,560
Does she know, too?

418
00:30:43,140 --> 00:30:45,190
   

419
00:30:45,190 --> 00:30:47,760
Why are you calling?

420
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:51,370
No, no. Don't do things like this.

421
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:52,870
 Hey, Lee Ddoong! 

422
00:30:52,870 --> 00:30:54,660
Hey!

423
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:05,910
She suddenly has an emergency at work.

424
00:31:14,770 --> 00:31:17,800
Kang Hu Yeong, consider yourself lucky.

425
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:20,760
I'm tolerating you since Hye Ji likes you.

426
00:31:23,890 --> 00:31:27,070
Why would she fall for someone like him?

427
00:31:29,850 --> 00:31:36,040
♫  I wonder why I'm being influenced by you  ♫

428
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:42,550
♫  It surprises me how I mimic the way you talk  ♫

429
00:31:42,550 --> 00:31:45,550
♫  It's so strange  ♫

430
00:31:50,710 --> 00:31:52,830
I'm sorry.

431
00:31:52,830 --> 00:31:55,180
You don't have to apologize to me.

432
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:56,660
That's how you feel.

433
00:31:56,660 --> 00:32:00,760
♫  Could you stop your heart from racing and shaking?  ♫

434
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:04,550
So did you look for Hong Ju purposely when you returned?

435
00:32:04,550 --> 00:32:06,900
I happened to run into her.

436
00:32:08,320 --> 00:32:10,600
You're Uncle Wook's nephew by chance.

437
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:13,260
You live downstairs from Lee Ddoong by chance.

438
00:32:13,260 --> 00:32:15,360
You hung out yesterday by chance.

439
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:17,960
Did you see her today by chance too?

440
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:20,490
Was all of it just a coincidence?

441
00:32:20,490 --> 00:32:24,320
♫  Will you respond to my feelings?  ♫

442
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:28,170
One part wasn't a coincidence.

443
00:32:28,170 --> 00:32:30,360
♫  Someday when you find out how I feel  ♫

444
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:36,130
By chance, since we were in high school...

445
00:32:36,130 --> 00:32:42,870
♫  You need to tell me, too  ♫

446
00:32:42,870 --> 00:32:46,390
♫  That you like me  ♫

447
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:53,530
Welcome.

448
00:32:54,390 --> 00:32:56,070
Hey, you came.

449
00:32:56,070 --> 00:32:58,080
How would you get any customers like that?

450
00:32:58,080 --> 00:33:02,370
You should greet a customer happily and energetically.

451
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:07,310
Customer, as if. You don't help the business at all.

452
00:33:07,310 --> 00:33:12,200
I've been telling everyone I meet that your restaurant is amazing.

453
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,460
You should pay me a commission. I'd own this building already.

454
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:17,130
How does that math work?

455
00:33:17,130 --> 00:33:20,980
How much commission would earn you a building even I can't afford?

456
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:23,280
Did you eat dinner?

457
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:25,170
Make me something tasty.

458
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:26,990
I gave up on fried chicken to come here.

459
00:33:26,990 --> 00:33:29,870
Got it. I'll make you something tasty.

460
00:33:34,660 --> 00:33:36,610
Hey, hold on.

461
00:33:36,610 --> 00:33:39,520
I'll only feed you.

462
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:43,360
Go to your friend if you need a therapist.

463
00:33:44,130 --> 00:33:46,160
My friend...

464
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:48,410
is having fried chicken with her first love right now.

465
00:33:48,410 --> 00:33:52,610
What? With Hu Yeong? Just those two?

466
00:33:52,610 --> 00:33:54,620
Yes.

467
00:33:56,940 --> 00:34:02,670
No matter how much I think, Hye Ji deserves so much better!

468
00:34:09,610 --> 00:34:13,220
Seriously, this makes no sense.

469
00:34:15,770 --> 00:34:20,190
Why shouldn't it make sense? But...

470
00:34:20,190 --> 00:34:23,750
Excuse me, we'll have another draft beer.

471
00:34:24,410 --> 00:34:26,640
I thought you couldn't drink.

472
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:31,630
Don't be sweet to me unless you're going to date me.

473
00:34:32,610 --> 00:34:34,150
Okay.

474
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:40,920
 Okay, I will stop now. 

475
00:34:42,670 --> 00:34:45,660
You've decided to stay in Korea, right?

476
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:51,240
Are you going back?

477
00:34:52,330 --> 00:34:56,350
Oh, I see, okay, okay.

478
00:34:56,350 --> 00:35:00,970
I thought you were serious because you got so emotional just now.

479
00:35:00,970 --> 00:35:04,400
You're like me, too. Do you want to test her?

480
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,890
It's not that.

481
00:35:06,890 --> 00:35:09,600
Do you know who is her number 0 on speed dial?

482
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:12,700
It's neither you nor Bang Jun Ho, who's been with her for years.

483
00:35:12,700 --> 00:35:15,080
It's me. I'm her guardian.

484
00:35:15,080 --> 00:35:17,920
You can't compete with me, anyway.

485
00:35:18,710 --> 00:35:20,800
I'll pay.

486
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:25,300
We didn't even touch the chicken. Take it with you. You can't have this in the U.S.

487
00:35:25,300 --> 00:35:29,410
   

488
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,780
I'll pay.

489
00:35:45,890 --> 00:35:49,460
I even made a side dish to feed you.

490
00:35:49,460 --> 00:35:51,000
When will you grow up?

491
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:53,610
I'm done growing. My height hasn't changed since Grade 9.

492
00:35:53,610 --> 00:35:55,900
Are you stupid?

493
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:59,870
Are you all serious right now? Why do you keep provoking me?

494
00:36:03,490 --> 00:36:04,900
I just pity Hu Yeong.

495
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:08,300
Why would you pity him? He's a total jerk and a rogue!

496
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:11,500
I, the Korean office worker, am more pitiable.

497
00:36:14,570 --> 00:36:16,730
 Why am I the only one eating this tasty food? 

498
00:36:16,730 --> 00:36:21,560
 How can you go to work if you start craving alcohol starting Monday? 

499
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:26,190
You need to give your liver a break—

500
00:36:35,390 --> 00:36:38,020
 Help yourself. Go ahead. 

501
00:36:48,150 --> 00:36:54,140
The CEO said I need to work on the tenth anniversary project.

502
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:03,550
You have to if the CEO tells you to. How dare you say no?

503
00:37:03,550 --> 00:37:05,090
She said she'd make me the main producer.

504
00:37:05,090 --> 00:37:09,300
That's great. I thought you've always wanted to be one?

505
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:13,600
Yes, it's my first opportunity since I started working ten years ago.

506
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:17,020
Is it already ten years? You got your chance after working so hard.

507
00:37:17,020 --> 00:37:19,650
It's Bang Jun Ho's book.

508
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:24,510
You'd better say no. You can speak up. You've worked there ten years.

509
00:37:24,510 --> 00:37:27,230
I'm finally becoming a senior producer after ten years, though.

510
00:37:27,230 --> 00:37:30,720
Would that get you a discount at convenience stores?

511
00:37:33,550 --> 00:37:35,060
Who else would do it if not me?

512
00:37:35,060 --> 00:37:36,910
Find a better thing to worry about.

513
00:37:36,910 --> 00:37:39,190
There are tons of people who would do it.

514
00:37:39,190 --> 00:37:42,090
But still, I'm a founding member.

515
00:37:42,090 --> 00:37:46,100
I need to work on the foundation anniversary project.

516
00:37:46,100 --> 00:37:49,400
Hong Ju, are you crazy? You want to work with Bang Jun Ho?

517
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,500
You still haven't come to your senses yet.

518
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:53,890
- I'm calling Hye Ji now. 
 - You're dead.

519
00:37:53,890 --> 00:37:57,350
You little... You knew you'd die when you said that, didn't you?

520
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:01,900
- What? 
 - Give me ramen noodles.

521
00:38:01,900 --> 00:38:04,100
Goodness! I'm so sick of this!

522
00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:12,300
   

523
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:26,850
 Yes, Lee Hong Ju is your problem now. 

