00:41:15,390 --> 00:41:17,850
I enjoyed your proposal.

548
00:41:17,850 --> 00:41:20,850
The overall quality isn't perfect, 
    

549
00:41:20,850 --> 00:41:22,430
but you chose a good book.

550
00:41:22,430 --> 00:41:27,060
I liked how you interpreted it as the audience.

551
00:41:29,750 --> 00:41:31,930
Thank you.

552
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:35,580
Hand me your resume.

553
00:41:35,580 --> 00:41:38,670
Weren't you told to bring it to the interview?

554
00:41:46,100 --> 00:41:47,600
   

555
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:50,000
Is this all? 
     

556
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,140
Yes.

557
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:54,750
This shouldn't be all.

558
00:41:57,490 --> 00:42:00,250
What did you think of Peter's Pen

559
00:42:00,250 --> 00:42:02,760
when you applied with such qualifications?

560
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:07,520
The application requirement said, "Anyone who loves animation."

561
00:42:07,520 --> 00:42:10,050
- It said the education level doesn't matter. 
 - That meant

562
00:42:10,050 --> 00:42:14,310
candidates with a basic education level.

563
00:42:14,310 --> 00:42:16,920
"Anyone who loves animation" refers to

564
00:42:16,920 --> 00:42:21,000
someone with professional skills as an animator.

565
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:23,500
Don't you know?

566
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:27,030
Is that so? I didn't know.

567
00:42:27,770 --> 00:42:30,710
I wrote it wrong. It was me.

568
00:42:30,710 --> 00:42:32,980
Okay then.

569
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:39,480
You can leave now.

570
00:42:40,780 --> 00:42:42,750
CEO Bae,

571
00:42:42,750 --> 00:42:44,920
you can make me do anything.

572
00:42:44,920 --> 00:42:47,400
I'll learn everything. I'll try everything.

573
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:50,960
I stayed up all night for the first time working on a proposal.

574
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:52,480
I have a dream, too.

575
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:58,760
I want youth like me to have fun and heartwarming dreams watching our films.

576
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:02,570
Just imagining that got me excited.

577
00:43:02,570 --> 00:43:07,700
And I'm sure of it now after meeting you.

578
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:09,140
This is the place.

579
00:43:09,140 --> 00:43:12,140
I want to work here.

580
00:43:12,140 --> 00:43:13,680
   

581
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:17,140
Did you have fun while working on this?

582
00:43:17,140 --> 00:43:18,530
Yes!

583
00:43:18,530 --> 00:43:20,700
How much?

584
00:43:20,700 --> 00:43:25,100
I didn't notice I stayed up all night. I didn't even notice the sunrise.

585
00:43:27,900 --> 00:43:29,720
   

586
00:43:59,190 --> 00:44:01,210
Hello.

587
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:05,580
CEO Bae.

588
00:44:05,580 --> 00:44:08,690
CEO Bae, I'll do it.

589
00:44:09,870 --> 00:44:11,720
Because of Mr. Bang? 
    

590
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:14,520
No. Well...

591
00:44:14,520 --> 00:44:17,010
To be honest, I'm not sure.

592
00:44:17,010 --> 00:44:19,930
I'm certain I'd regret this moment later.

593
00:44:19,930 --> 00:44:22,500
But I'd regret today if I didn't.

594
00:44:22,500 --> 00:44:24,500
I'll just do it.

595
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:28,900
I want to become a main producer through this project.

596
00:44:32,400 --> 00:44:36,890
If you can't separate work and life, I'll remove you at that time.

597
00:44:36,890 --> 00:44:38,680
Deal!

598
00:44:59,230 --> 00:45:01,720
Are you sure you can leave like this?

599
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:03,840
Is this really your answer?

600
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:06,130
I'm done with work.

601
00:45:06,130 --> 00:45:09,410
We could have taken my car to the airport.

602
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:16,190
Tell your employees that they did a good job.

603
00:45:18,730 --> 00:45:22,050
Did you say goodbye to Lee Ddoong?

604
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:25,020
She knows I'm leaving.

605
00:45:25,020 --> 00:45:26,890
And...

606
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:30,720
she said goodbye when she saw me.

607
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:33,060
And you're okay with that?

608
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:38,800
I think that's enough, given the relationship we have.

609
00:45:41,250 --> 00:45:44,730
Call me when you arrive then.

610
00:45:44,730 --> 00:45:47,150
See you in the States, Uncle. 
    

611
00:46:02,900 --> 00:46:05,200
Ready.

612
00:46:05,200 --> 00:46:07,220
Throw it! Throw it!

613
00:46:07,220 --> 00:46:10,000
Here I go!

614
00:46:16,990 --> 00:46:19,100
Yes, yes!

615
00:46:20,810 --> 00:46:22,860
Hey, hey, hey!

616
00:46:22,860 --> 00:46:24,650
Pass it!

617
00:46:29,010 --> 00:46:31,400
   

618
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:34,030
   

619
00:46:34,030 --> 00:46:36,010
   

620
00:46:36,010 --> 00:46:38,070
   

621
00:46:38,070 --> 00:46:41,070
   

622
00:46:41,070 --> 00:46:45,100
 Hye Ji, is something going on? 

623
00:46:48,500 --> 00:46:51,900
   

624
00:46:59,890 --> 00:47:02,040
Kim Hye Ji...

625
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:05,350
why are you so pathetic?

626
00:47:08,340 --> 00:47:09,740
Rematch. Start.

627
00:47:09,740 --> 00:47:12,220
Teacher Son, can we stop playing the bodyguard game?

628
00:47:12,220 --> 00:47:14,820
That's right. We get hit instead of the girls.

629
00:47:14,820 --> 00:47:16,510
It's unfair.

630
00:47:16,510 --> 00:47:20,740
Really? Okay. I'll listen to you.

631
00:47:20,740 --> 00:47:27,310
It's unfair that only you got to experience protecting someone.

632
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:31,250
You threw it yourself earlier. That was cool.

633
00:47:31,250 --> 00:47:33,870
I never did.

634
00:47:33,870 --> 00:47:37,530
We get it, you're Superman. Who is he trying to protect?

635
00:47:38,430 --> 00:47:40,750
Over here! Over here! Over here!

636
00:47:40,750 --> 00:47:43,010
Goodness, here we go.

637
00:47:43,630 --> 00:47:46,420
Catch it! Catch it!

638
00:47:47,140 --> 00:47:49,460
Let's go! Let's go!

639
00:47:49,460 --> 00:47:52,110
Stop right there!

640
00:47:57,700 --> 00:47:59,750
Teacher Son.

641
00:48:04,230 --> 00:48:06,380
Over here.

642
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:19,950
Teacher Son, can I ask you something?

643
00:48:19,950 --> 00:48:22,700
Yes, go ahead.

644
00:48:22,700 --> 00:48:26,240
Well, if...

645
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:33,380
your first love likes your best friend, how would you feel?

646
00:48:33,380 --> 00:48:35,130
It's a coincidence,

647
00:48:35,130 --> 00:48:38,570
but they're getting tangled up by fate.

648
00:48:44,430 --> 00:48:46,370
I would

649
00:48:46,370 --> 00:48:50,590
congratulate them

650
00:48:51,510 --> 00:48:54,170
if my friend finds a new love, at least.

651
00:48:54,170 --> 00:48:57,740
My first love is turning 60 next year.

652
00:48:58,710 --> 00:49:02,360
But it's not because she's 60.

653
00:49:02,360 --> 00:49:05,880
My buddy is a good person, too.

654
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:09,780
I've wanted him to find someone good,

655
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:12,210
but my first love is a good person, too.

656
00:49:12,210 --> 00:49:14,610
Since they're both good...

657
00:49:14,610 --> 00:49:16,300
yes...

658
00:49:17,630 --> 00:49:20,920
Thinking about it, I think it's a good thing.

659
00:49:23,990 --> 00:49:25,560
What?

660
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:35,470
Come on now.

661
00:49:36,700 --> 00:49:40,350
Seriously, so funny.

662
00:49:41,380 --> 00:49:45,840
Did you refuse to meet Teacher Oh's niece, by the way?

663
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:48,590
- Yes. 
 - Why did you?

664
00:49:48,590 --> 00:49:51,260
I'll ask her to arrange the date again.

665
00:49:51,260 --> 00:49:53,890
N-No, Ms. Kim! Ms. Kim!

666
00:49:53,890 --> 00:49:58,030
Forget I asked you to have a date with Hong Ju, okay?

667
00:50:15,120 --> 00:50:18,520
Right, Sang Pil.

668
00:50:23,460 --> 00:50:25,460
   

669
00:50:37,370 --> 00:50:40,130
I'm breaking my promise again.

670
00:50:47,590 --> 00:50:49,400
 I'm here for a visit. 

671
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:51,440
 Who are you visiting in which squadron? 

672
00:50:51,440 --> 00:50:54,350
 "Squadron"? Just one second. 

673
00:50:58,250 --> 00:51:00,180
 Here. 

674
00:51:01,780 --> 00:51:04,960
 Squadron No. 1 is no longer here. 

675
00:51:05,770 --> 00:51:08,620
 I've been sending letters here until last week. 

676
00:51:08,620 --> 00:51:10,720
 This reply came from here too. 

677
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:14,130
 I can't check the details for you. 

678
00:51:14,130 --> 00:51:17,470
   

679
00:51:43,320 --> 00:51:47,040
   

680
00:51:48,390 --> 00:51:53,080
   

681
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:20,220
 I must be crazy. 

682
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:22,630
 Why did I follow her here? 

683
00:52:33,030 --> 00:52:34,940
 Let's go. 

684
00:52:43,210 --> 00:52:45,150
 Only one bus comes here. 

685
00:52:45,150 --> 00:52:48,120
 We have to walk to the terminal if we miss it. 

686
00:53:03,900 --> 00:53:06,430
 Do you want to eat ramen before we go? 

687
00:53:10,920 --> 00:53:12,890
   

688
00:53:12,890 --> 00:53:17,930
   

689
00:53:26,390 --> 00:53:29,180
 You aren't students from around here. 
   

690
00:53:29,180 --> 00:53:33,320
 We came to visit someone at the army base here. 

691
00:53:33,320 --> 00:53:37,020
But we didn't get to see him.

692
00:53:37,020 --> 00:53:40,840
If you think you'll never see them again, you can endure it,

693
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:44,940
but you miss them if you know they're nearby.

694
00:53:46,110 --> 00:53:48,350
I tend to make food spicy.

695
00:53:48,350 --> 00:53:51,230
Get water if the ramen is too spicy.

696
00:53:51,230 --> 00:53:53,770
Enjoy, okay?

697
00:53:53,770 --> 00:53:56,060
 Thank you for the food. 

698
00:54:10,870 --> 00:54:12,960
It's spicy.

699
00:54:15,500 --> 00:54:19,980
Her ramen is really spicy.

700
00:54:19,980 --> 00:54:23,530
The ramen is too spicy, Ma'am.

701
00:54:24,460 --> 00:54:26,550
It's spicy.

702
00:54:31,560 --> 00:54:34,390
Hey, why are you suddenly crying?

703
00:54:34,390 --> 00:54:38,390
It's spicy. The ramen is too spicy.

704
00:54:39,430 --> 00:54:40,790
 Should I add some water? 

705
00:54:40,790 --> 00:54:44,020
No. That'd ruin it.

706
00:55:04,060 --> 00:55:05,180
 Eat slowly. 

707
00:55:05,180 --> 00:55:07,600
We have time to catch the bus.

708
00:55:07,600 --> 00:55:10,360
Go without me. I'll stay here overnight.

709
00:55:10,360 --> 00:55:12,360
You can't stay overnight here.

710
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:15,250
I'll confess my love to Oppa and leave.

711
00:55:15,250 --> 00:55:17,850
You don't even know if he's here. How would you do that?

712
00:55:17,850 --> 00:55:21,620
I will. I'll find him and tell him.

713
00:55:22,930 --> 00:55:26,030
It's overflowing from here.

714
00:55:26,030 --> 00:55:30,030
It keeps overflowing that I can't even breathe.

715
00:55:30,030 --> 00:55:32,930
I think I'd die if I don't tell him.

716
00:55:36,630 --> 00:55:38,300
Still, you can't.

717
00:55:38,300 --> 00:55:40,840
Don't confess.

718
00:55:40,840 --> 00:55:42,410
Why not?

719
00:55:43,210 --> 00:55:45,100
Because...

720
00:55:52,190 --> 00:55:54,420
I will report you,

721
00:55:55,220 --> 00:55:58,070
for dating a soldier when you're a student.

722
00:56:00,680 --> 00:56:03,440
You'd report me? Are you crazy?

723
00:56:03,440 --> 00:56:07,340
He gave you the wrong address because he doesn't want you to visit.

724
00:56:07,340 --> 00:56:10,860
You'd get rejected anyway. Isn't it better not to see him?

725
00:56:12,010 --> 00:56:15,240
You aren't rejected yet.

726
00:56:29,720 --> 00:56:33,290
She hit me with a spoon first.

727
00:56:43,270 --> 00:56:45,690
Why do you keep crying?

728
00:56:56,900 --> 00:56:59,380
 Do you want kimbap? 

729
00:56:59,380 --> 00:57:01,870
 Ice cream? 

730
00:57:01,870 --> 00:57:03,710
Chocolate?

731
00:57:07,670 --> 00:57:12,230
Then should we go back to the army base after this?

732
00:57:18,260 --> 00:57:22,510
Okay. Let's go and ask.

733
00:57:24,630 --> 00:57:27,540
Eat. The noodles will get soggy.

734
00:57:31,900 --> 00:57:33,900
   

735
00:57:37,260 --> 00:57:39,800
She's been sending letters here,

736
00:57:39,800 --> 00:57:42,600
and she got a reply here too.

737
00:57:42,600 --> 00:57:45,910
Bang Jun Ho of Squadron No. 1 at this army base. Right?

738
00:57:45,910 --> 00:57:48,200
This is the right army base,

739
00:57:48,200 --> 00:57:52,800
but Squadron No. 1 is no longer here. I told you.

740
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:57,000
"No longer" means they used to be here and left.

741
00:57:57,000 --> 00:57:59,610
- Tell me where they went. 
 - That's...

742
00:57:59,610 --> 00:58:03,140
classified military information. I can't tell you.

743
00:58:18,400 --> 00:58:22,520
You can deliver a letter and present, right?

744
00:58:22,520 --> 00:58:26,770
Student, this isn't a janitor's office.

745
00:58:26,770 --> 00:58:31,760
Tell me where they went so we can deliver them ourselves.

746
00:58:41,820 --> 00:58:45,040
Squadron No. 1 was sent to the general outpost last week.

747
00:58:45,040 --> 00:58:47,770
They went up to the mountain over there.

748
00:58:47,770 --> 00:58:50,320
You can't visit them for six months.

749
00:58:50,320 --> 00:58:52,150
Happy now?

750
00:58:54,390 --> 00:58:56,920
Six...

751
00:59:09,240 --> 00:59:14,370
   

752
00:59:30,700 --> 00:59:33,840
Lee Hong Ju, let's walk a bit faster.

753
00:59:33,840 --> 00:59:36,010
The bus will be arriving soon.

754
00:59:36,010 --> 00:59:38,340
I'm coming.

755
00:59:38,340 --> 00:59:40,270
Coming.

756
00:59:47,640 --> 00:59:51,340
If he went somewhere she couldn't visit,

757
00:59:51,340 --> 00:59:53,890
he should have written her.

758
00:59:53,890 --> 00:59:56,380
What's wrong with that scum?

759
01:00:08,160 --> 01:00:10,050
   

760
01:00:10,050 --> 01:00:11,360
Hey, that's the last bus.

761
01:00:11,360 --> 01:00:14,200
Run, Kang Hu Yeong!

762
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:29,600
- The bus... 
 - Are you okay?

763
01:00:29,600 --> 01:00:31,200
The bus!

764
01:00:31,200 --> 01:00:34,600
You should have stopped the bus!

765
01:00:34,600 --> 01:00:35,900
But you fell—

766
01:00:35,900 --> 01:00:37,200
That's not important right now.

767
01:00:37,200 --> 01:00:39,500
What if we miss the bus to Seoul now?

768
01:00:39,500 --> 01:00:42,390
We can stay here overnight then.

769
01:00:42,390 --> 01:00:43,610
Why would I sleep with you?

770
01:00:43,610 --> 01:00:45,180
When did I say that?

771
01:00:45,180 --> 01:00:47,590
Of course, we'd sleep separately.

772
01:00:51,930 --> 01:00:53,300
 Gosh, I'm sorry. 

773
01:00:53,300 --> 01:00:56,300
That car suddenly cut me off.

774
01:00:56,300 --> 01:00:58,690
It's okay.

775
01:01:01,210 --> 01:01:03,350
We can arrive at the airport by three, right?

776
01:01:03,350 --> 01:01:07,410
Of course. We're leaving Seoul now.

777
01:01:14,200 --> 01:01:16,290
   

778
01:01:20,460 --> 01:01:21,560
   

779
01:01:30,210 --> 01:01:33,610
- Yes, Hye Ji, I— 
  - Where are you right now, Hu Yeong? 

780
01:01:33,610 --> 01:01:35,500
I'm on my way to the airport.

781
01:01:35,500 --> 01:01:38,830
Hong Ju was in a car accident.

782
01:01:38,830 --> 01:01:42,760
- What? 
  - She's being sent to Ohbok Hospital's ER now. 

783
01:01:42,760 --> 01:01:45,460
I'm her guardian. What do I do?

784
01:01:45,460 --> 01:01:48,690
 I'll be there soon, but she's probably alone now. 

785
01:01:48,690 --> 01:01:49,870
 Could you get there before me? 

786
01:01:49,870 --> 01:01:51,780
Please turn around, Sir.

787
01:01:51,780 --> 01:01:53,240
Let's go to Ohbok Hospital.

788
01:01:53,240 --> 01:01:55,260
You'd miss the flight if we turned around—

789
01:01:55,260 --> 01:01:57,720
It doesn't matter. Hurry.

790
01:01:57,720 --> 01:01:59,510
Okay.

791
01:02:04,260 --> 01:02:06,280
 You went off-route. 

792
01:02:06,280 --> 01:02:09,250
 Finding a new route. 

793
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:13,300
♫  I feel so strange these days  ♫

794
01:02:13,300 --> 01:02:18,970
♫  For some reason, all day I think of you  ♫

795
01:02:18,970 --> 01:02:21,310
Sir, your suitcase!

796
01:02:21,310 --> 01:02:25,620
♫  I can't stop worrying about you  ♫

